modules.description: This module encodes and decodes strings using Base64 encoding as defined in RFC 4648. It supports custom alphabets, including a URI-safe variant, and provides functions for both strict and result-based error handling. Use cases include safely encoding binary data for transmission over media designed for ASCII strings, such as embedding images in JSON or URLs.

This module decodes and encodes Base64 (RFC2045) data, handling input from strings, channels, or manual buffers and outputting to strings, channels, or manual buffers. It processes data incrementally, returning decoded bytes or encoded characters as they become available, and supports error detection such as malformed input or incorrect padding. Concrete use cases include decoding Base64-encoded network data or encoding binary data for transmission over text-based protocols.
